Porting WISE Application to any other server will require few changes in the configuration files, and source files.

Changes to the source files:
1. survey/main.js 
   modify two lines stating
   window.parent.opener.location.replace('http://localhost:8080/WISE/survey/abort.htm')	 
   to point to the correct host.
   
2. survey/thanks.htm
   modify the line
   {document.write("<p>You could now review the results of the survey. Please click the link to <a href='http://localhost:8080/WISE/survey/"+review_arg+"'>review the survey results.</a>")}

3. survey/wise_outer_frame_test.htm
   modify the src=... to correct url.
   
   
Changes to the configuration file

1. xml/dme/fileXX.xml where XX is the latest file
      update the Forward_On= attribute
      
2. localwise.properties 
		update the server.rootURL
	
3. wisetest.properties
		update admin.server and dme.server
		
Update wisetest.properties: 
mysql.server = sagedb.arc2.ucla.edu
